---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import SectionHeading from "../components/SectionHeading.astro";
import Card from "../components/Card.astro";

const title = "Uses · Usman Shahid";
const description =
  "What I run day-to-day — infrastructure tooling, AI assistants, languages, and the stack behind the AI Agent Platform at Careem.";
---

<Base title={title} description={description} path="/uses/">
  <section class="max-w-[980px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <SectionHeading
      eyebrow="Uses"
      title="What I run"
    />
    <p
      class="text-[--color-text-soft] leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-[680px] text-[17px]"
    >
      The tools and stacks I reach for daily — mix of production infrastructure
      work at Careem and the AI tooling I use to ship faster.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5 items-start">
      <Card>
        <h3
          class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[--color-accent] mb-4"
        >
          AI assistants &amp; agentic tooling
        </h3>
        <ul
          class="space-y-3 text-[--color-text-muted] text-[15px] leading-relaxed"
        >
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Claude Code</strong> &mdash;
            primary daily driver for engineering work. Multi-agent
            orchestration, custom skills, MCP-connected workflows. Daily
            user.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Cursor</strong> &mdash; in-IDE
            pair-programming when I want to stay in the editor surface.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">GitHub Copilot</strong> &mdash;
            inline completion for boilerplate-heavy code.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Gemini</strong> &mdash; second
            opinion on prompts and longer-context reasoning tasks.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Model Context Protocol (MCP)</strong>
            &mdash; building production MCP servers for the AI Agent Platform at
            Careem. Wrote the <a
              href="https://usmanshahid.medium.com/llm-tool-calling-series-part-2-enabling-mcp-on-your-existing-microservices-bfc9ce7dc67f"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer">primer on retrofitting microservices</a
            >.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </Card>

      <Card>
        <h3
          class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[--color-accent] mb-4"
        >
          Cloud &amp; Kubernetes
        </h3>
        <ul
          class="space-y-3 text-[--color-text-muted] text-[15px] leading-relaxed"
        >
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">AWS EKS</strong> &mdash;
            production daily. Managed control plane, custom data plane
            (Karpenter, ARM/Spot fleets).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Karpenter</strong> &mdash;
            consolidation, Spot interruption handling, custom NodePools and
            NodeClasses. The 40% EKS cost cut leaned heavily on this.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">VPA</strong> &mdash; rightsizing
            in steady-state workloads after Karpenter handled the bin-packing.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">ArgoCD</strong> &mdash; GitOps
            for everything. At Intech I wired it to Keycloak for auditable
            Helm-based deploys.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Helm + Kustomize</strong>
            &mdash; both, picked per workload shape.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">operator-sdk (Go)</strong>
            &mdash; built a bespoke Kubernetes Ingress Operator for bare-metal
            clusters at Intech.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </Card>

      <Card>
        <h3
          class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[--color-accent] mb-4"
        >
          Networking &amp; gateway
        </h3>
        <ul
          class="space-y-3 text-[--color-text-muted] text-[15px] leading-relaxed"
        >
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Kong</strong> &mdash;
            consolidated 12 legacy gateways onto one Kong cluster at ~10k RPS
            with 99.99% uptime during cutover. Built a GitOps-driven bespoke
            control plane for route management.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Linkerd</strong> &mdash; service
            mesh for mTLS and observability without the ops cost of Istio.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Flagger</strong> &mdash;
            progressive delivery / automated canaries on top of Linkerd.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">OpenResty (LuaJIT)</strong>
            &mdash; dynamic proxying + JWT bearer auth back at Intech; still
            a tool I reach for when nginx alone won't cut it.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </Card>

      <Card>
        <h3
          class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[--color-accent] mb-4"
        >
          Observability
        </h3>
        <ul
          class="space-y-3 text-[--color-text-muted] text-[15px] leading-relaxed"
        >
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Prometheus + Thanos</strong>
            &mdash; long-retention, high-cardinality metric storage across the
            EKS fleet.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Grafana</strong> &mdash; SLO
            dashboards, cost-tracking, on-call runbooks.
          </li>
          <li>
            Google SRE <strong class="text-[--color-text]"
              >golden signals</strong
            > (latency / traffic / errors / saturation) as the default mental
            model for instrumentation.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </Card>

      <Card>
        <h3
          class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[--color-accent] mb-4"
        >
          Infrastructure as code &amp; CI/CD
        </h3>
        <ul
          class="space-y-3 text-[--color-text-muted] text-[15px] leading-relaxed"
        >
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Terraform + Terragrunt</strong>
            &mdash; multi-environment, multi-account provisioning. Took new
            service provisioning from days to minutes at Careem.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Ansible</strong> &mdash;
            bare-metal cluster provisioning and config drift remediation.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Docker</strong> &mdash; every
            workload, every environment.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">GitLab CI / GitHub Actions</strong>
            &mdash; both, depending on the org. This site deploys via GH
            Actions with <code class="text-[--color-text]">--ignore-scripts</code>
            on <code class="text-[--color-text]">npm ci</code> as a supply-chain
            mitigation.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </Card>

      <Card>
        <h3
          class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[--color-accent] mb-4"
        >
          Languages
        </h3>
        <ul
          class="space-y-3 text-[--color-text-muted] text-[15px] leading-relaxed"
        >
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Go</strong> &mdash; operators,
            tooling, anything that needs to run as a tight binary.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Python</strong> &mdash; the
            glue. Agent platform tooling, automation scripts.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Java</strong> &mdash; legacy
            service surfaces and Spring-based identity providers from the
            Intech era.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">C# / .NET</strong> &mdash; from
            the Alachisoft days building NCache and NosDB internals. Still
            reach for it when working in mature .NET shops.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </Card>

      <Card>
        <h3
          class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[--color-accent] mb-4"
        >
          This site
        </h3>
        <ul
          class="space-y-3 text-[--color-text-muted] text-[15px] leading-relaxed"
        >
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Astro</strong> with the minimal
            template, static output, zero JS shipped by default except for the
            theme toggle.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Tailwind CSS v4</strong> via the
            Vite plugin, with custom <code class="text-[--color-text]"
              >@theme</code
            > tokens.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">Inter Variable</strong>
            self-hosted as a single woff2.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-[--color-text]">GitHub Pages</strong> via GH
            Actions, deployed in ~36 seconds end-to-end.
          </li>
          <li>
            OG card generated programmatically with Playwright from <code
              class="text-[--color-text]">scripts/og-template.html</code
            >. Source: <a
              href="https://github.com/codemug/codemug.github.io"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer">github.com/codemug/codemug.github.io</a
            >.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </Card>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-10 text-sm text-[--color-text-dim]">
      Inspired by the long-running <a
        href="https://uses.tech"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">uses.tech</a
      > community.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
